<p>Thanks, <sub>oops, not exactly but i did run some of the details past some of those experts in question and referenced the Internet a lot</sub>, thanks and yes, the <em>djinn</em> are specifically designed to add a faerie-ish, Seelie Court-esq urban fantasy underground political whatever to the ORIA universe, and yes, very much a secular/religious organization. Basically, my idea for ORIA is that the core or nucleus was founded very Horizon Initiative-style, where people of different origins, cultures, and religions came together for a shared goal (i.e. protecting the Middle East and other predominantly Muslim regions from outside interference and colonization, as well as to manage the fairly fragile human<em>/Djinn</em> alliance). The Ayatollahs tolerate its less-than-orthodox nature because a) ORIA serves too useful a purpose in keeping Iran stable in the world of the paranormal and anomalous, and b) ORIA is still a fairly secret organization and its members are very clearly instructed to remain apolitical and try to moderate their views publicly.</p>

